  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In the spring of 1941, my father was sent to another camp called Camp Les Milles.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That's C-A-M-P, new word L-E-S, and new word, capital M-I-L-E-S-- M-I-L-L-E-S, which is located just north of Marseilles, France.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The camp actually was a former brick factory.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And because they were limited as to how often they could write and how much they could write, one page per person per week, in order to stay in touch with each other-- that is my mother and father to stay in touch with each other and also with me, my father would write one page and then send it to my mother, and she would write on the reverse page and then forward it to me.",
      "word_count": 81
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the following week, my mother would write one page, send it to my father.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He write on the reverse page, send it to me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I could write as often and as much as I wanted to.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "At one point, it was possible to send money to my parents.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I understand there was a canteen there where you could supplement your diet.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Food was extremely expensive, plus the Nazis skimmed off quite a bit at the-- from the amount that was sent.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I didn't really have any money.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I was working, but I was just barely scratching out of a living.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I had a stamp collection that I had taken out of Germany illegally.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I sold that stamp collection and used that money to send to my parents.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I tried to find other sources where I could maybe get some money to send to my parents and wasn't really successful in doing so.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I had lost contact with Mrs.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
